-### Round 1 — awaiting follow-up review
+### Round 1 — addressed
+
+**Bug: submission mutability leak.** `submit()` now deep-copies the
+submission before storing; `read_submission()` deep-copies on return.
+`EvaluateSubmission.metrics` is a dict (not frozen) so the ``frozen``
+dataclass alone wasn't enough — the deep copy is the fix. New test
+`TestReadIsolation.test_submission_metrics_mutation_does_not_leak`
+verifies both the caller-side mutation and the reader-side mutation
+cannot change the committed submission.
+
+**Bug: malformed submissions still crashed instead of routing to
+`validation_error`.** The store now exposes `validate_terminal(task_id)`
+returning ``(decision, reason)`` where ``decision`` is one of
+``accept`` / ``reject_worker`` / ``reject_validation``. The driver
+consults this before every terminal decision. Additions:
+
+- `_validate_implement_acceptance` now dry-runs
+  `_validated_update(trial, commit_sha=…)`, so an invalid SHA
+  surfaces as ``reject_validation`` instead of raising.
+- `_validate_evaluate_acceptance` now dry-runs the full trial write
+  (status=success, metrics, artifacts_uri, completed_at), catching
+  invalid URIs before the real update.
+- New `_validate_evaluate_error` covers the error path: a
+  `status="error"` evaluate submission with schema-invalid metrics
+  is routed to ``reject_validation`` rather than blowing up inside
+  `_reject_evaluate`.
+- `_reject_evaluate` now skips trial writes whenever
+  `reason=="validation_error"` (treated like `eval_error`: trial
+  stays in ``starting``, task is terminal with no invalid field
+  landing on the trial).
+
+Tests updated: `TestFieldValidationOnUpdate` now asserts end-to-end
+terminalization — invalid `commit_sha` / `artifacts_uri` produce
+`task.failed(validation_error)` and the invalid values never land
+on the trial. `TestMetricsSchemaValidationIndependentOfSuccess` now
+asserts that an error submission with bad metrics also becomes
+`validation_error` with no trial mutation.
+
+**Risk: `events()` still snapshot-only (no `read_range` / replay /
+subscription).** Accepted; Phase 5's scope is the state machine and
+transactional invariant, and the snapshot surface is sufficient for
+the in-process scripted workers and tests. A conforming subscription
+/ replay API is a Phase 6 concern, where the storage backend becomes
+real. Documented explicitly in the module docstring.
+
